Loop :  Loop is used to excute a task multiple times unit a specif condition is true.

Types of Loop:

1. while loop
2. do while 
3. for loop
	Nested for Loop 
_______________________________________________________________________________________________
1. while Loop: It is an Entry Control Loop. In which condition is checked before entering the loop.
	It will execute the while block if and only if the condition is true.

Syntax:
		intialization;

		while(condition)
		{
			Statements;
			inc/dec;
		}


2. do while : It is an exit control loop, In which condition is checked after executing the statements once. In this it will execute the statement once even the condition is false .


Syntax:
	initialization;

	do
	{
			statements;
			inc/dec;
	}while(condition);